				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$BAI= HC\; (cm)/{Height }^{1.5}(m)\; (HC: Hip \ Circumference)$$\end{document}

A new approach that standardizes waist circumference measurement based on height and BMI, known as the A Body Shape Index (ABSI), has been proposed for determining abdominal obesity [39]. ABSI has been shown to accurately reflect visceral fat [40, 41] and is a good indicator of skeletal muscle loss [42–44]. Furthermore, high ABSI values are positively correlated with both morbidity and mortality risk [45].\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
