				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ABSI= WC/\; ({BMI}^\frac{2}{3} \times {Height}^\frac{1}{2})\; (WC: waist \ circumference,\; BMI: Body \ mass \ index)$$\end{document}

The Conicity Index (CI), developed for screening abdominal obesity, is an index that includes measurements of body weight, height, and waist circumference [46]. Conicity Index is most associated with cardiometabolic diseases and parallels body fat percentage [47, 48].\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
